I really like looking out and seeing nothing.

56:44.860 --> 56:47.112
It's like being in a spaceship.

57:07.216 --> 57:08.633
Welcome back.

57:08.675 --> 57:10.177
You know, I sympathize with astronauts

57:10.219 --> 57:12.096
who haven't walked on firm ground.

57:12.137 --> 57:13.722
We were only there for six hours.

57:13.764 --> 57:15.933
What was your favorite part?

57:15.974 --> 57:18.810
I liked being inside the orb.

57:18.852 --> 57:22.022
Like, you just imagine we're in a metal sphere in the ocean.

57:22.064 --> 57:25.276
It's kind of a little trippy inside,

57:22.064 --> 57:25.276
with all the red buttons.

57:25.317 --> 57:28.195
We could be anywhere in the universe.

57:30.488 --> 57:32.699
[Victoria] I really love looking at the samples

57:32.741 --> 57:34.410
when they come up the seashore.

57:34.451 --> 57:37.913
Kind of like every Alvin dive is Christmas morning.

57:37.955 --> 57:39.456
You know? The samples come up,

57:39.497 --> 57:42.167
and we get to go and look

57:42.209 --> 57:43.668
at what people collected.

57:45.963 --> 57:49.007
My hope is that eventually, one day

57:49.049 --> 57:50.801
we'll be able to really understand

57:50.842 --> 57:52.552
how microbial ecosystems tick.

57:52.594 --> 57:54.554
I don't think this is

57:54.596 --> 57:57.141
even a ten-year achievable goal.

57:58.350 --> 58:00.852
It's been almost like this,

58:00.894 --> 58:03.063
this long-term obsession.

58:03.105 --> 58:04.856
The projects that I work on

58:04.898 --> 58:06.984
are a multi-year investment.

58:08.235 --> 58:09.569
Maybe many people

58:09.611 --> 58:11.238
who aren't in the sciences...

58:11.280 --> 58:13.407
A lot of times, you just see a finished product

58:13.449 --> 58:16.243
of a nice publication.

58:16.285 --> 58:18.662
And we rarely write in the publication,

58:18.703 --> 58:20.789
"We spent three years doing

58:20.831 --> 58:23.208
all of these other things before this finally worked."

